            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Cuttsia viburnea? F.v.M. ¶  ¶  ¶  ¶ Saxifrageae ¶  ¶ Flowers from Tallebudgera ¶  ¶ Capsules from Coochin ¶  ¶ I doubt the idendity of the plant from which I gathered the flowers and capsules. It l...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.00.00d</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Benedetto Scortechini</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M127, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Cuttsia%20viburnea">Cuttsia viburnea</name>
                     </seg>(MEL 2235712). MS annotation on reverse: '1881 Scoterchini'. The letter's handwriting is similar to that of known specimens of Scortechini's handwriting.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Cuttsia%20viburnea">Cuttsia viburnea</name>? F.v.M.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Saxifrageae">Saxifrageae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Flowers from Tallebudgera<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Southeastern Qld.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Capsules from Coochin<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Qld.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I doubt the idendity of the plant from which I gathered the flowers and capsules. It looks much the same; I gathered the capsules long ago, the flowers only lately in two far apart localities. I have no access to your description in the V vol. of the Frag:<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B65.07.03, p. 47.</p>
               </note> from the generic description in the Genera Plantarum<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), vol. 1, p. 1004.</p>
               </note> I am inclined to think that the present specimen is a Cuttsia.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cuttsia%20viburnea">Cuttsia viburnea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Saxifrageae">Saxifrageae</name>
            </p>
